BALANCE DEFECTS FOUND AND CORRECTED
1. Civilization Lv.1 consumed more opening resources than the required facilities and assault loop could sustain. The project now requires a compact contribution, two basic towers, one barrier, 20 kills, one base destruction, one artifact and a five-minute healthy-city streak.
2. City HP could fall below a civilization threshold with no recovery path. The city now starts passive reconstruction 120 seconds after damage at 0.08 HP/s.
3. Several initial hostile bases could stack their first waves on one road front. Placement now prefers unused angular sectors and progressively delays/throttles bases forced onto the same front.
4. Hostile bases had no immediate defense against direct assault. Each hostile base now launches one saved, non-duplicating guard force on first direct attack.
5. Civilization Lv.4 required obsolete captured outposts that new games do not generate. The requirement now uses three active simple bases.
6. Major and simple bases could be established without resource cost. Expansion and rebuilding now consume tier-appropriate processed resources.

DESIGN BOUNDARIES PRESERVED
- Destroying a hostile base still creates a physical recovery item rather than granting resources remotely.
- Retrieval squads, manual GPS recovery, squad recovery/reorganization and remote regional progression remain unchanged in purpose.
- Combat squads still travel the road graph and can be intercepted or destroyed.
- The save key and schema version remain unchanged; missing recovery state is normalized for older saves.
- No obsolete parallel balance system or compatibility-only project requirement remains active.

